FIELD.name: csc_name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source name in the format '2CXO Jhhmmss.s{+|-}ddmmss[X]'

FIELD.name: csc_ra_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source position, ICRS right ascension

FIELD.name: csc_dec_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source position, ICRS declination

FIELD.name: csc_err_ellipse_r0_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Major radius of the 95% confidence level position error ellipse

FIELD.name: csc_err_ellipse_r1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Minor radius of the 95% confidence level position error ellipse

FIELD.name: csc_err_ellipse_ang
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Position angle (ref. local true north) of the major axis of the 95% confidence level error ellipse

FIELD.name: csc_significance_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Highest flux significance (S/N) across all stacked observations and energy bands

FIELD.name: csc_likelihood
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Highest detection log likelihood across all stacked observations and energy bands

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_b_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events; ACIS

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_lolim_b_1

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_hilim_b_1

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_w_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events; HRC w

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_lolim_w_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% l

FIELD.name: csc_flux_aper_hilim_w_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% u

FIELD.name: csc_conf_flag_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source may be confused (source and/or background regions overlap in one or more contributing stacked observations)

FIELD.name: csc_dither_warning_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Highest statistically significant peak in the power spectrum of the source region count rate occurs at the dither frequency or at a beat frequency of the dither frequency in one or more observations

FIELD.name: csc_extent_flag_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source is extended, or deconvolved source extent is inconsistent with a point source at the 90% confidence level in one or more observations and energy bands

FIELD.name: csc_pileup_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS pile-up fraction exceeds ~ 10% in all observations; source properties may be affected

FIELD.name: csc_sat_src_flag_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source is saturated in all observations; source properties are unreliable

FIELD.name: csc_streak_src_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source is located on an ACIS readout streak in all observations; source properties may be affected

FIELD.name: csc_var_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source displays flux variability within one or more observations, or between observations, in one or more energy bands

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hm_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - medium (1.2-2.0 keV) energy band hardness ratio

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hm_lolim_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - medium (1.2-2.0 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% lower confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hm_hilim_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - medium (1.2-2.0 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% upper confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hs
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hs_lolim
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% lower confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_hard_hs_hilim
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS hard - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% upper confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_hard_ms_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS medium - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio

FIELD.name: csc_hard_ms_lolim_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS medium - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% lower confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_hard_ms_hilim_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ACIS medium - soft (0.5-1.2 keV) energy band hardness ratio (68% upper confidence limit)

FIELD.name: csc_var_intra_index_b_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Intra-observation Gregory-Loredo variability index in the range [0, 10]: indicates whether the source region photon flux is constant within an observation (highest value across all observations); ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_intra_prob_b
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Intra-observation Gregory-Loredo variability probability (highest value across all observations); ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_intra_index_w_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Intra-observation Gregory-Loredo variability index in the range [0, 10]: indicates whether the source region photon flux is constant within an observation (highest value across all observations); HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_intra_prob_w
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Intra-observation Gregory-Loredo variability probability (highest value across all observations); HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_inter_index_b_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Inter-observation variability index in the range [0, 10]: indicates whether the source region photon flux is constant between observations; ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_inter_prob_b
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Inter-observation variability probability, calculated from the chi^2 distribution of the photon fluxes of the individual observations; ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_inter_index_w_1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Inter-observation variability index in the range [0, 10]: indicates whether the source region photon flux is constant between observations; HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_var_inter_prob_w
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Inter-observation variability probability, calculated from the chi^2 distribution of the photon fluxes of the individual observations; HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: csc_acis_num
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total number of ACIS imaging observations contributing to the Master Sources Table record of the source

FIELD.name: csc_hrc_num
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total number of HRC imaging observations contributing to the Master Sources Table record of the source

FIELD.name: csc_acis_time
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total exposure time (seconds of good time) for all ACIS imaging observations contributing to the Master Sources Table record of the source

FIELD.name: csc_hrc_time
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Total exposure time (seconds of good time) for all HRC imaging observations contributing to the Master Sources Table record of the source
